台灣大學寫作教學中心-英文寫作基礎



















「英文寫作基礎」課，課程內容著重於培養學生寫作時能活用文法概念，正確使用專業學術用字及其搭配詞，並能透過正確的文章結構，適切地表達自己的意見與看法。因此，此類課程除了教授不同的篇章結構、組織與寫作技巧外，還使用了本中心研究團隊，針對台灣研究生所設計的學術文法與學術字彙教材，培養學生核心文法與字彙能力，以為學術寫作奠下扎實的基礎。
Aims and Objectives
This course intends to equip graduate students with fundamental skills of writing English for academic purposes. Topics to be covered include essential vocabulary in academic English, basic English sentence structures, and common patterns for English paragraph/essay writing.
Course Content
Patterns of Paragraph/Essay Writing

Paragraph and Essay Structure
Unity and Coherence
Process Paragraphs/Essays
Cause/Effect Paragraphs/Essays
Comparison/Contrast Paragraphs/Essays
Classification Paragraphs/Essays
Argument Essays

Sentence Structures

Types of Sentences
Fixing Sentence Problems
Noun Clauses
Adverb Clauses
Adjective Clauses
Participial Phrases

Grammar foci

Article
Referential Expressions
Subject-verb Agreement
Tenses and Aspects
Passive Voice
Modal Verbs
Infinitives and Gerunds
Transitional Signals

Academic Word List
Course Intended Learning Outcome (CILO)
By the end of the course, students should be able to:

CILO 1:  Demonstrate familiarities with vocabulary frequently used in academic discourse
CILO 2:  Identify and edit their own sentence problems
CILO 3:  Apply their knowledge of English grammar for writing purposes
CILO 4:  Understand common rhetoric modes in English paragraph/essay writing

Teaching and Learning Activities (TLAs)

Students will learn how to use online corpora with various concordancing functions for checking the collocational patterns of the vocabulary in Academic Word List and further make up sentences using the expressions. (CILO 1)
Students will analyze various aspects of English grammar by analyzing the journal articles in their own disciplines, devising their own generalizations and checking them against the accounts in the grammar textbooks. (CILO 2 and 3)
Students will write a group essay following a specific rhetorical mode based on common interests. Each student will be in charge of one paragraph and needs to cooperate to make the whole essay coherent in terms organization, content, and diction. (CILO 4)
Students will peer-review one another’s paragraphs/essays and give comments on the works with regard to word choice, grammar usage, and organization. (CILO 2 and 4)

Assessment Methods



Types of Assessment
Weighting
CILOs to be addressed
Descriptions of Assessment Tasks




Writing Assignments
35%
2, 3, 4
Students need to write 3 paragraphs or essays that follow specific rhetorical modes.


Written Exercises
20%
2, 3, 4
Students will do short writing drills such as sentence completion and combination.


Vocabulary Quizzes
10%
1, 2
The quizzes will test students’ knowledge of the collocational patterns of academic vocabulary.


Grammar Analysis
10%
2, 3
Students need to apply their grammatical knowledge to analyzing the journal articles in their own disciplines.


Final Exam
15%
1, 2, 3, 4
The exam will cover Academic Word List and grammatical structures. It will also require students to write a paragraph/essay.


Participation
10%
-
Based on the students’ participation in class discussions, online peer-review and attendance.



Textbooks

Oshima, A., and Hogue, A. (2006). Writing academic English (4th ed.). White Plains, NY: Pearson/Longman.
Martin L. Armaudet and Mary Ellen Barrett. (1990). Paragraph Development: A Guide for Students of English (2nd ed.). White Plains, NY: Prentice Hall Regents.
臺大寫作教學中心教材編輯小組。《活用文法結構：捷進學術英文寫作關鍵》。臺北：國立臺灣大學出版中心，2011。
臺大寫作教學中心教材編輯小組。《活用學術字彙：跨出論文寫作的第一步》。臺北：國立臺灣大學出版中心，2010。










